.TH "sys_sched_getaffinity" 9 "sys_sched_getaffinity" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
sys_sched_getaffinity \- get the CPU affinity of a process
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "long" sys_sched_getaffinity
.BI "(pid_t pid "  ","
.BI "unsigned int len "  ","
.BI "unsigned long __user * user_mask_ptr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pid" 12
pid of the process
.IP "len" 12
length in bytes of the bitmask pointed to by user_mask_ptr
.IP "user_mask_ptr" 12
user-space pointer to hold the current CPU mask
.SH "RETURN"
size of CPU mask copied to user_mask_ptr on success. An
error code otherwise.
